  "articleSummary": "This tutorial argues that formatting numbers and currency requires separating locale-specific display rules (e.g., decimal separators, symbol placement) from the global value of a currency (ISO 4217 code). It explains that numbers are local (vary by user locale) while currency is global (value unchanged by locale), and recommends client-side formatting using JavaScript’s `Intl.NumberFormat`. The article targets developers building ecommerce or payment systems, using a conversational tone with emoji icons and the recurring framing “Numbers are Local, Currency is Global.”",
